article.headline: Yale 68, Vermont 52
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Greg Mangano scored 22 points and grabbed 15 rebounds in Yale's 68-52 win over Vermont on Saturday. Mangano, who averaged 16.3 points and 10 rebounds per game last season, recorded his fourth double-double of the season. Austin Morgan and Jeremiah Kreisberg had 14 points each for the Bulldogs, who won their third straight. Yale (5-2) took its first lead, 4-2, behind a Kreisberg layup and wouldn't look back from there. The Bulldogs used a 20-9 run to take a 24-11 lead with 10:11 to play in the half. Yale led 38-20 at halftime. The Bulldogs shot 48 percent (23 of 48) from the field, compared to just 35 percent (21 of 60) for Vermont. Vermont (4-4) forced Yale to commit 16 turnovers but was outrebounded 39-29 and only made 54 percent (7 of 13) of their free throws. Four McGlynn led Vermont with 16 points.
